    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hi @lukasavic,\r\n\r\nWhich version of react-instantsearch are you currently using? \r\n\r\nOn the last version, the URL Syncing has to be implemented by the user typically to allow more advance use cases like yours. To synchronize an `InstantSearch` with an URL you need to handle the `InstantSearch` state externally like described here: https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/v2/docgen/src/guide/Routing.md. \r\nYou can also find the guide about multiple indices here: https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/v2/docgen/src/guide/Multi%20index.md\r\n\r\nBe careful, the API described in those guides has not been entirely released yet so I suggest you wait for a couple of days before trying it. Those guides will also be available [on our documentation website](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/react/).\r\n\r\nBasically the idea is to listen to every state changes for both indices and create your URL accordingly. Then, when you'll need to update the `InstantSearch` state, you will take your url and  reconstruct the state based on your previous conventions. \r\n",
