    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Please open a new issue, but as said before, url sync / routing takes whole ownership of the url, and therefore can only be present for one InstantSearch instance at a time, unless you pass a custom router that reads and writes in a relevant part of the URL.\n\nYou can also hoist the InstantSearch instance and only have one present on the page for both tabs.",
